description: Circular MIL Spec Connector CONNECTOR, PLASTIC, REAR MOUNT, SQUARE RECEPTACLE, LESS CONTACTS, 18-11, 5 POLE, PIN, ROHS
info:
APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors have a 3-start ACME thread and 2-way bayonet design for fast coupling. These lightweight, corrosion-resistant connectors feature a robust design for rugged environments and are durable to 500 mating cycles. This connector series is ROHS compliant, can withstand current up to 30A, and has an insulation resistance of 500M at 500VDC. The connectors feature a self-locking mechanism and are rated at IP67 when mated. APC Connectors also comply with UL 94 V-0 flammability and are UV resistant and F1-rated. Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors are designed for use in various applications, including industrial machinery, agricultural machinery, factory automation, materials handling equipment, communications equipment, HVAC, lighting and signage, and rail and transit vehicles and systems.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells
info:
Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps are a RoHS compliant replacement for cadmium plating. The black-zinc, nickel-finish clamps are a cost-effective cable holding option over cadmium and offer environmental protection. The series is available in a variety of shell sizes (11 through 48), both military (MIL) specification and commercial types, and with EMI/RFI shielding. The clamps clean-up the cable after termination and provide good strain relief at the termination area. Amphenol Pcd Black Zinc Nickel Finish Backshell Clamps are can be used as a replacement for cadmium plating in aeronautical and military applications.

info:
PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors were developed to transfer high power (500V) in harsh environments with full safety for the user. The circular connectors offer an IP28 rating, tested pressure watertight (48h, under 2m water), and allows a finger test for socket contacts and inserts. Depending on the shell and backshell plating option, the PowerSafe connectors operate in a temperature range as low as -65°C and up to +200°C. The Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors are ideal for use in defense, avionics, and harsh industrial markets.

info:
Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps help to tidy up the cable after termination and provide strain relief at the termination area. The clamps are offered in environmental and non-environmental options, as well as EMI/RFI. The components are available in black zinc nickel, adding to the existing finishes in olive drab gray cadmium, tin, or nickel with a variety of shell sizes 11 through 48. Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps meet MIL-DTL-38999, MIL-DTL-26482 Series II, MIL-DTL-83723 Series I and II, MIL-DTL-24308, and MIL-DTL-83513.
